var e={pathwayGroups:{cns:{label:"CNS / Hypothalamus",color:"#7c3aed"},brainstem:{label:"Brainstem",color:"#6366f1"},reward:{label:"Reward / Hedonic",color:"#ec4899"},gut:{label:"Gut & Incretins",color:"#0284c7"},pancreas:{label:"Pancreas",color:"#0d9488"},adipose:{label:"Adipose Tissue",color:"#f59e0b"},metabolism:{label:"Energy Expenditure",color:"#dc2626"},genetics:{label:"Genetic Loci",color:"#475569"},environment:{label:"Environment",color:"#16a34a"}},pathwayNodes:[{id:"arc",label:"Arcuate Nucleus",group:"cns",r:24,refs:["melanocortin_physiology","melanocortin_review","leptin_insulin_cns"],desc:"Primary integration hub for peripheral energy signals; contains POMC and NPY/AgRP neuron populations"},{id:"pomc",label:"POMC / CART",group:"cns",r:18,refs:["melanocortin_physiology","leptin_insulin_cns","genetics_monogenic"],desc:"Anorexigenic neurons producing \u03B1-MSH; activated by leptin and insulin to suppress appetite"},{id:"npy_agrp",label:"NPY / AgRP",group:"cns",r:18,refs:["melanocortin_physiology","leptin_insulin_cns"],desc:"Orexigenic neurons; AgRP antagonizes MC4R, NPY promotes feeding. Activated by ghrelin, inhibited by leptin"},{id:"mc4r",label:"MC4R",group:"cns",r:20,refs:["melanocortin_physiology","mc4r_sns_signaling","genetics_monogenic"],desc:"Melanocortin-4 receptor: master switch for appetite. Loss-of-function \u2192 most common monogenic obesity"},{id:"pvn",label:"PVN",group:"cns",r:16,refs:["melanocortin_physiology","mc4r_sns_signaling"],desc:"Paraventricular nucleus: drives sympathetic outflow, thyroid axis, and CRH/stress responses"},{id:"lh",label:"Lateral Hypo.",group:"cns",r:14,refs:["melanocortin_physiology"],desc:"Contains orexin and MCH neurons; integrates homeostatic signals with arousal and reward"},{id:"leptin_r",label:"Leptin Resistance",group:"cns",r:15,refs:["leptin_insulin_cns","genetics_monogenic"],desc:"In common obesity, high leptin but blunted central signaling (SOCS3, PTP1B, ER stress, inflammation)"},{id:"nts",label:"NTS",group:"brainstem",r:18,refs:["brainstem_autonomic"],desc:"Nucleus tractus solitarius: receives vagal afferents from gut; integrates satiety signals (CCK, PYY, GLP-1)"},{id:"ap",label:"Area Postrema",group:"brainstem",r:13,refs:["brainstem_autonomic"],desc:"Circumventricular organ; senses circulating hormones (amylin, GLP-1) without blood-brain barrier"},{id:"vta",label:"VTA",group:"reward",r:16,refs:["reward_dopamine_food"],desc:'Ventral tegmental area: dopaminergic neurons driving food "wanting" and reward prediction'},{id:"nacc",label:"Nucleus Accumbens",group:"reward",r:15,refs:["reward_dopamine_food"],desc:'Integrates dopamine reward signals; opioid and endocannabinoid systems modulate food "liking"'},{id:"pfc",label:"Prefrontal Cortex",group:"reward",r:14,refs:["reward_dopamine_food"],desc:"Executive control, decision-making about food; impaired inhibitory control linked to overeating"},{id:"gi",label:"GI Tract",group:"gut",r:22,refs:["gut_hormones_appetite"],desc:"Source of multiple satiety and incretin hormones; bariatric surgery remodels this signaling dramatically"},{id:"glp1",label:"GLP-1",group:"gut",r:18,refs:["gut_hormones_appetite","glp1_mechanism_review"],desc:"From L-cells; suppresses appetite (brainstem + hypothalamus), slows gastric emptying, enhances insulin secretion"},{id:"gip",label:"GIP",group:"gut",r:14,refs:["gut_hormones_appetite"],desc:"From K-cells; incretin effect on insulin; GIP-R agonism may enhance weight loss in combination with GLP-1"},{id:"pyy",label:"PYY\u2083\u208B\u2083\u2086",group:"gut",r:13,refs:["gut_hormones_appetite","brainstem_autonomic"],desc:"Peptide YY: released postprandially from L-cells; signals satiety via vagal afferents and hypothalamus"},{id:"cck",label:"CCK",group:"gut",r:12,refs:["gut_hormones_appetite","brainstem_autonomic"],desc:"Cholecystokinin: short-term satiety signal from I-cells; acts on vagal afferents to NTS"},{id:"ghrelin",label:"Ghrelin",group:"gut",r:16,refs:["ghrelin_hunger","gut_hormones_appetite"],desc:"Only peripheral orexigenic hormone; rises pre-meal, falls post-meal; activates NPY/AgRP neurons"},{id:"pancreas",label:"Pancreas",group:"pancreas",r:20,refs:["gut_hormones_appetite"],desc:"\u03B2-cells secrete insulin and amylin; \u03B1-cells secrete glucagon. Central to glucose homeostasis and adiposity signaling"},{id:"insulin",label:"Insulin",group:"pancreas",r:16,refs:["leptin_insulin_cns"],desc:"CNS adiposity signal (crosses BBB \u2192 hypothalamic IR \u2192 PI3K/Akt); peripherally promotes fat storage and glucose uptake"},{id:"amylin",label:"Amylin",group:"pancreas",r:13,refs:["gut_hormones_appetite"],desc:"Co-secreted with insulin; acts on area postrema to reduce appetite. Analog cagrilintide in clinical trials"},{id:"glucagon",label:"Glucagon",group:"pancreas",r:12,refs:["gut_hormones_appetite"],desc:"Promotes hepatic glucose output and energy expenditure; glucagon receptor agonism part of triple agonist strategy"},{id:"wat",label:"White Adipose",group:"adipose",r:22,refs:["adipose_inflammation"],desc:"Primary energy storage; secretes leptin, adiponectin, inflammatory cytokines. Visceral WAT \u2192 higher metabolic risk"},{id:"bat",label:"Brown Adipose",group:"adipose",r:16,refs:["bat_thermogenesis"],desc:"UCP1-expressing thermogenic fat; activated by SNS/cold; increases energy expenditure. Therapeutic target"},{id:"leptin",label:"Leptin",group:"adipose",r:18,refs:["leptin_insulin_cns","genetics_monogenic"],desc:"Proportional to fat mass; signals energy sufficiency to hypothalamus. Deficiency \u2192 severe obesity; resistance \u2192 common obesity"},{id:"adiponec",label:"Adiponectin",group:"adipose",r:12,refs:["adiponectin_review"],desc:"Reduced in obesity; improves insulin sensitivity, anti-inflammatory and anti-atherogenic effects"},{id:"inflam",label:"Inflammation",group:"adipose",r:15,refs:["adipose_inflammation"],desc:"Adipocyte hypertrophy \u2192 hypoxia \u2192 macrophage infiltration \u2192 TNF-\u03B1, IL-6 \u2192 systemic insulin resistance"},{id:"sns",label:"Sympathetic NS",group:"metabolism",r:17,refs:["mc4r_sns_signaling"],desc:"Drives BAT thermogenesis (\u03B23-AR), WAT lipolysis; modulated by leptin and melanocortin signaling via PVN"},{id:"thyroid",label:"Thyroid Axis",group:"metabolism",r:15,refs:["thyroid_metabolism"],desc:"TRH\u2192TSH\u2192T3/T4; increases basal metabolic rate. Weight loss reduces T3, lowering expenditure (adaptive thermogenesis)"},{id:"muscle",label:"Skeletal Muscle",group:"metabolism",r:18,refs:["thyroid_metabolism"],desc:"Major glucose/lipid sink; fiber type, mitochondrial content affect expenditure. NEAT is a major variable"},{id:"liver",label:"Liver",group:"metabolism",r:17,refs:["adipose_inflammation"],desc:"Hepatic glucose output, lipogenesis, FGF21 production. Central insulin resistance \u2192 increased gluconeogenesis"},{id:"fgf21",label:"FGF21",group:"metabolism",r:12,refs:["fgf21_obesity"],desc:"Hepatokine promoting glucose uptake, fatty acid oxidation, and WAT browning. Analog efruxifermin in trials"},{id:"fto",label:"FTO / IRX3/5",group:"genetics",r:16,refs:["gwas_loci","gwas_replicated"],desc:"First robust BMI GWAS locus; acts via IRX3/IRX5 regulation of adipocyte thermogenesis and developmental programming"},{id:"mc4r_gene",label:"MC4R gene",group:"genetics",r:15,refs:["genetics_monogenic","gwas_loci"],desc:"Most common monogenic obesity gene; heterozygous LoF in 1\u20135% of severe childhood obesity. Hyperphagia + high lean mass"},{id:"lep_gene",label:"LEP / LEPR genes",group:"genetics",r:14,refs:["genetics_monogenic"],desc:"Rare monogenic: leptin or receptor deficiency \u2192 severe hyperphagic obesity. Leptin replacement curative for LEP deficiency"},{id:"pomc_gene",label:"POMC / PCSK1",group:"genetics",r:13,refs:["genetics_monogenic"],desc:"Defects reduce \u03B1-MSH production \u2192 impaired melanocortin signaling. Associated with early-onset obesity, adrenal insufficiency"},{id:"bdnf",label:"BDNF / SH2B1",group:"genetics",r:12,refs:["genetics_monogenic","gwas_loci"],desc:"Neurotrophin pathway in hypothalamic circuits; loss-of-function \u2192 hyperphagic obesity + cognitive phenotypes"},{id:"prs",label:"Polygenic Risk",group:"genetics",r:14,refs:["gwas_loci","heritability_bmi","gene_environment","gwas_integration"],desc:'>1000 common variants, mostly CNS-expressed genes. ~40-70% heritability. Risk alleles "unmasked" in obesogenic environments'},{id:"diet",label:"Diet / Food Env.",group:"environment",r:17,refs:["gene_environment"],desc:"Calorie-dense, ultra-processed foods; cheap availability; portion sizes. Primary environmental driver of epidemic"},{id:"activity",label:"Physical Activity",group:"environment",r:15,refs:["gene_environment"],desc:"Reduced activity + sedentary behavior; NEAT is highly variable and genetically influenced"},{id:"stress",label:"Stress / Sleep",group:"environment",r:13,refs:["stress_cortisol_obesity"],desc:"Psychosocial stress \u2192 cortisol \u2192 visceral fat; sleep disruption \u2192 ghrelin \u2191, leptin \u2193, impaired glucose tolerance"}]};export{e as a};
